The paper deals with algorithms for computing the earth-mover distance between two multisets of points in a two-dimensional grid. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses sketching and approximation algorithms, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and data mining (cs.DM).
